## ✅ `.gitignore`

The `.gitignore` file tells Git which files and directories to ignore when pushing changes to the repository. Here’s a simple template for your project:

```gitignore
# Node modules (if you use any Node-based tools)
node_modules/

# Log files
*.log

# MacOS-specific files
.DS_Store

# Windows-specific files
Thumbs.db

# Editor-specific files (VS Code, etc.)
.vscode/

# IDE specific files
.idea/

# NPM or Yarn lock files
package-lock.json
yarn.lock

# Minified JS file generated during build
*.min.js

# Generated directories or build outputs
/dist
/build

# Miscellaneous temporary files
*.tmp
